<h3 class="listing__header">Annie Zunz Ward</h3>

<p>Annie Zunz Ward has 28 beds and cares for patients with endocrinological conditions such as diabetes. It was opened in 1913 and is named after Annie Zunz, the widow of a German merchant who lived in London. In 1912 King's received Â£10,000 from the trustees of the Annie Zunz Bequest on condition a ward was named after her.</p>
